            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is cooking, wash your<strong> lettuce </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper, remove 1 <strong>outer</strong> <strong>leaf</strong> per person and set aside, then cut the <strong>inner core </strong>into wedges</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese </strong>and combine with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a pot and mix until the cheese is fully coated</p><p>Add your <strong>mustard ketchup</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to the pot and set aside for later – this is your <strong>cheese sauce base</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
